From 23162dab9015046e15cdcd3b8efaa3fc72646133 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 05:17:12 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] landing: match nav to reference design, add global light/dark
 theme toggle
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- Nav CTA now shows a single outline 'Book a test' button (matches
  design reference) instead of duplicate View reports + solid button.
- Added an always-visible sun/moon theme toggle button in the top nav
  (desktop) and a matching row in the mobile drawer, wired to the
  existing ThemeService so it flips [data-theme=dark] on <html> and
  re-themes the entire app (all pages, all palettes), not just the
  landing page.
- Wrapped nav-cta + theme toggle + hamburger in a new .lp-nav-right
  flex group so right-edge alignment is preserved at every breakpoint.
- No changes to src/styles.css — default Teal/Indigo theme is
  untouched.
---
